# Project Context for Gemini CLI

This file provides persistent context to Gemini CLI about your project.
Customize this for your specific project.

## Tech Stack
- Language: (e.g., TypeScript, Python, Go)
- Framework: (e.g., Next.js, Django, Gin)
- Database: (e.g., PostgreSQL, MongoDB)
- ORM: (e.g., Prisma, SQLAlchemy)

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── api/          # API routes/handlers
├── components/   # UI components
├── lib/          # Shared utilities
├── models/       # Data models
└── tests/        # Test files
```

## Key Commands
```bash
# Development
npm run dev          # Start dev server

# Testing
npm test             # Run all tests
npm run test:watch   # Watch mode

# Code Quality
npm run lint         # Run linter
npm run typecheck    # Type checking

# Database
npm run db:migrate   # Run migrations
npm run db:seed      # Seed database
```

## Conventions
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- API routes: RESTful, versioned under /api/v1/
- Tests: Co-located with source files as *.test.ts
- Commits: Conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, etc.)

## Important Patterns
- All API endpoints should validate input with Zod schemas
- Database queries should use transactions for multi-step operations
- Components should use the existing design system in /components/ui/

## Environment
- Node.js 22
- npm (not yarn or pnpm)
- PostgreSQL 16
